etymologies: early 20th century: from para-‘alongside’ + sympathetic, because some of these nerves run alongside sympathetic nerves

definitions: relating to the part of the automatic nervous system that counterbalances the action of the sympathetic nerves. It consists of nerves arising from the brain and the lower end of the spinal cord and supplying the internal organs, blood vessels, and glands.
shortDefinitions: relating to part of autonomic nervous system which balances action of sympathetic nerves
